Program: Free Thinking
Title: Rebecca Solnit, Truth, National Poetry Day
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0008wc1
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 3 Oct 2019
Who holds the power? The US activist and author Rebecca Solnit talks to Shahidha Bari about pros and cons of anger, US border patrols, rape cases in courts and shifts in the point of view of Hollywood films. Plus a look at the theme of National Poetry Day 2019 - Truth with the poet David Cain author of Truth Street - A Hillsborough Poem and Fiona Benson - whose collection is called Vertigo & Ghost. Rebecca Solnit's fourth Essay collection is called Whose Story Is This ? Old Conflicts, New Chapters. Producer: Torquil MacLeod Show less